Note:
Julia Translation Round-Trip Probe
.
End-to-end proof that the Julia translation pipeline is REAL, not a skeleton:
.
    Julia source
      -> julia_lexer    (create_lexer / tokenize)
      -> julia_parser   (create_parser / parse_program -> ASTNode tree)
      -> julia_to_hir   (lower the ASTNode tree to the hir.runa dict/list HIR)
      -> hir_to_julia   (emit HIR back to valid Julia text)
      -> re-lex / re-parse / re-lower of the emitted text (HIR2)
      -> structural + CONTENT equality on the key constructs
.
The Julia HIR node model is hir.runa's dictionary/list literal interchange shared
by julia_to_hir (producer) and hir_to_julia (consumer): a dictionary is a
HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL whose entries List (16-byte [key, value] blocks) hangs at
the children slot; a list is a HIR list literal whose elements List hangs at the
children slot; string payloads are HIR string-literal nodes read with
get_string_literal_value. This probe reads HIR fields through exactly that
contract (the decoders below mirror the producer/consumer).
.
DEPTH: the probe does NOT merely check that nodes exist. On the RE-PARSED HIR2 it
asserts the CONTENTS survive the full round-trip:
    - at least six top-level function names recovered by name
    - a `::Int` typed parameter lowered to a type_annotation param
    - a default / keyword argument (a `= default` on a parameter)
    - an if / elseif / else chain (>= 2 branch dicts plus the else block)
    - a for-loop with its iterator variable + iterable
    - a struct's typed fields (>= 2 type_annotation fields)
    - an array comprehension with a generator AND a filter clause
    - a Dict literal whose keys survive
    - a string literal carrying interpolation ($(...))
.
A translator that dropped any of these (empty body, vanished params, lost filter)
makes the probe FAIL.
.
Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed).
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/julia/julia_to_hir.runa" as JuliaFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/julia/hir_to_julia.runa" as JuliaBackend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: hir.runa dict/list literal decoders (mirror the producer/consumer contract)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
A Julia HIR dictionary is a HIR_DICTIONARY_LITERAL whose entries List hangs at the
children slot. Each entry is a 16-byte block: key (raw string handle) at offset 0,
value (a child HIR node or HIR string literal) at offset 8. This decoder linear-
scans those entries comparing the raw key with string_equals, returning the stored
value. It is the exact lookup hir_to_julia's get_dictionary_value performs.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_get" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let entries be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with node
    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc size from List with entries
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let entry be proc get_at from List with entries, index
        If entry is not equal to 0:
            Let entry_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 0
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with entry_key, key
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 8
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
String fields ("node_type", "name", "operator", "value", ...) are stored as HIR
string literal nodes. This helper resolves the key then unwraps the literal to its
char* payload via get_string_literal_value.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_get_string" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value_node be proc dict_get with node, key
    If value_node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_string_literal_value from HIR with value_node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the backing element List of a HIR list literal so the probe can iterate
body statements, parameters, fields, generators and pairs.
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_elements" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_list_elements from HIR with node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Element count of a HIR list node (0 when absent).
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_count" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let items be proc list_elements with node
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc size from List with items
End Process

@Reasoning:
i-th element of a HIR list node (0 when out of range / absent).
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_at" takes node as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Let items be proc list_elements with node
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_at from List with items, index
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when a node's node_type tag equals the requested kind.
@End Reasoning
Process called "node_is" takes node as Integer, kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Let nt be proc dict_get_string with node, "node_type"
    If nt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, kind
End Process

@Reasoning:
Finds a top-level "function" member by name within the module body list. Returns
the function dict or 0.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_function" takes body as Integer, want_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Let count be proc list_count with body
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc list_at with body, index
        Let is_fn be proc node_is with item, "function"
        If is_fn is equal to 1:
            Let item_name be proc dict_get_string with item, "name"
            If item_name is not equal to 0:
                Let ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with item_name, want_name
                If ok is equal to 1:
                    Return item
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Counts "function" members in the module body list.
@End Reasoning
Process called "count_functions" takes body as Integer returns Integer:
    Let count be proc list_count with body
    Let found be 0
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc list_at with body, index
        Let is_fn be proc node_is with item, "function"
        If is_fn is equal to 1:
            Set found to found plus 1
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return found
End Process

@Reasoning:
Finds the first top-level member with the requested node_type tag.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_member" takes body as Integer, kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Let count be proc list_count with body
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc list_at with body, index
        Let ok be proc node_is with item, kind
        If ok is equal to 1:
            Return item
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Recursively searches a HIR subtree for the first node tagged with the requested
kind. Used to locate an expression (Dict literal, comprehension, if) nested inside
a function body without hard-coding the path. Bounded by structural recursion over
dict entries and list elements.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_deep" takes node as Integer, kind as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let here be proc node_is with node, kind
    If here is equal to 1:
        Return node
    End If

    Let entries be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with node
    If entries is not equal to 0:
        Let ecount be proc size from List with entries
        Let ei be 0
        While ei is less than ecount:
            Let entry be proc get_at from List with entries, ei
            If entry is not equal to 0:
                Let val be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 8
                Let found be proc find_deep with val, kind
                If found is not equal to 0:
                    Return found
                End If
            End If
            Set ei to ei plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Let elems be proc get_list_elements from HIR with node
    If elems is not equal to 0:
        Let lcount be proc size from List with elems
        Let li be 0
        While li is less than lcount:
            Let el be proc get_at from List with elems, li
            Let found2 be proc find_deep with el, kind
            If found2 is not equal to 0:
                Return found2
            End If
            Set li to li plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Counts type_annotation members in a list of parameters / struct fields, so the
probe can assert typed params and typed fields survive.
@End Reasoning
Process called "count_type_annotations" takes list_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let count be proc list_count with list_node
    Let found be 0
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc list_at with list_node, index
        Let ok be proc node_is with item, "type_annotation"
        If ok is equal to 1:
            Set found to found plus 1
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return found
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when a parameter list contains a default / keyword argument, modelled by
the frontend as a binary_op with the "=" operator wrapping the parameter.
@End Reasoning
Process called "params_have_default" takes list_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let count be proc list_count with list_node
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let item be proc list_at with list_node, index
        Let is_bin be proc node_is with item, "binary_op"
        If is_bin is equal to 1:
            Let op be proc dict_get_string with item, "operator"
            If op is not equal to 0:
                Let eq be proc string_equals from StringCore with op, "="
                If eq is equal to 1:
                    Return 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when a string-literal node's raw lexeme value contains a "$(" sequence,
i.e. it carries interpolation. The lexeme keeps quotes and interpolation verbatim
so the check is a substring scan over the value payload (36 == '$', 40 == '(').
@End Reasoning
Process called "string_has_interpolation" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let value be proc dict_get_string with node, "value"
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with value
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than len:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, i
        If ch is equal to 36:
            Let nexti be i plus 1
            If nexti is less than len:
                Let ch2 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value, nexti
                If ch2 is equal to 40:
                    Return 1
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Locates the first string literal anywhere in a function body that carries
interpolation, by structural recursion over dict entries and list elements.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_interpolated_string" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let is_lit be proc node_is with node, "literal"
    If is_lit is equal to 1:
        Let kind be proc dict_get_string with node, "literal_kind"
        If kind is not equal to 0:
            Let is_str be proc string_equals from StringCore with kind, "string"
            If is_str is equal to 1:
                Let has_interp be proc string_has_interpolation with node
                If has_interp is equal to 1:
                    Return node
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let entries be proc get_dictionary_entries from HIR with node
    If entries is not equal to 0:
        Let ecount be proc size from List with entries
        Let ei be 0
        While ei is less than ecount:
            Let entry be proc get_at from List with entries, ei
            If entry is not equal to 0:
                Let val be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entry, 8
                Let f be proc find_interpolated_string with val
                If f is not equal to 0:
                    Return f
                End If
            End If
            Set ei to ei plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Let elems be proc get_list_elements from HIR with node
    If elems is not equal to 0:
        Let lcount be proc size from List with elems
        Let li be 0
        While li is less than lcount:
            Let el be proc get_at from List with elems, li
            Let f2 be proc find_interpolated_string with el
            If f2 is not equal to 0:
                Return f2
            End If
            Set li to li plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
The module body list lives under the "body" key of the root "module" dict.
@End Reasoning
Process called "module_body" takes root as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc dict_get with root, "body"
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Depth probes shared by the HIR1 and HIR2 passes
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Runs the full content-depth assertion battery against one HIR module (used for both
the original HIR1 and the round-trip HIR2). Records each result in the shared
TestResults. The `tag` string distinguishes the two passes in the summary output.
@End Reasoning
Process called "assert_depth" takes results as Integer, root as Integer, tag as String returns Integer:
    Let body be proc module_body with root

    Note: --- six function names ---
    Let fn_count be proc count_functions with body
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "module has >= 6 functions", fn_count, 6

    Let f_area be proc find_function with body, "area"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'area' present", f_area
    Let f_scale be proc find_function with body, "scale"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'scale' present", f_scale
    Let f_classify be proc find_function with body, "classify"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'classify' present", f_classify
    Let f_sum_loop be proc find_function with body, "sum_loop"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'sum_loop' present", f_sum_loop
    Let f_evens be proc find_function with body, "evens"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'evens' present", f_evens
    Let f_config be proc find_function with body, "config"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'config' present", f_config
    Let f_greet be proc find_function with body, "greet"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "function 'greet' present", f_greet

    Note: --- a ::Int typed param on area(r::Int) ---
    Let area_params be proc dict_get with f_area, "parameters"
    Let area_typed be proc count_type_annotations with area_params
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "area has a typed (::Int) param", area_typed, 1

    Note: --- a default / keyword arg on scale(x, factor = 2) ---
    Let scale_params be proc dict_get with f_scale, "parameters"
    Let scale_has_default be proc params_have_default with scale_params
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "scale has a default-valued param", scale_has_default, 1

    Note: --- if / elseif / else inside classify ---
    Let classify_body be proc dict_get with f_classify, "body"
    Let if_node be proc find_deep with classify_body, "if_statement"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "classify contains an if statement", if_node
    Let branches be proc dict_get with if_node, "branches"
    Let branch_count be proc list_count with branches
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "if has >= 2 branches (if + elseif)", branch_count, 2
    Let else_block be proc dict_get with if_node, "else_block"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "if has an else block", else_block

    Note: --- for loop inside sum_loop ---
    Let sum_body be proc dict_get with f_sum_loop, "body"
    Let for_node be proc find_deep with sum_body, "for_loop"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "sum_loop contains a for loop", for_node
    Let for_var be proc dict_get with for_node, "iterator_variable"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "for loop has an iterator variable", for_var
    Let for_iter be proc dict_get with for_node, "iterable"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "for loop has an iterable", for_iter

    Note: --- struct with typed fields ---
    Let struct_node be proc find_member with body, "struct_definition"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "module has a struct definition", struct_node
    Let struct_fields be proc dict_get with struct_node, "fields"
    Let typed_fields be proc count_type_annotations with struct_fields
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "struct has >= 2 typed fields", typed_fields, 2

    Note: --- array comprehension with generator + filter inside evens ---
    Let evens_body be proc dict_get with f_evens, "body"
    Let comp_node be proc find_deep with evens_body, "list_comprehension"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "evens contains a comprehension", comp_node
    Let generators be proc dict_get with comp_node, "generators"
    Let gen_count be proc list_count with generators
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "comprehension has >= 1 generator", gen_count, 1
    Let comp_filter be proc dict_get with comp_node, "filter"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "comprehension has a filter clause", comp_filter

    Note: --- Dict keys inside config: `Dict("a" => 1, "b" => 2)` parses as a
    Note: call to Dict whose arguments are `pair` nodes, the idiomatic Julia
    Note: spelling. We assert the call carries >= 2 pair arguments (the keys). ---
    Let config_body be proc dict_get with f_config, "body"
    Let dict_pair be proc find_deep with config_body, "pair"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "config contains a Dict key/value pair", dict_pair
    Let dict_call be proc find_deep with config_body, "call"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "config contains the Dict(...) call", dict_call
    Let dict_args be proc dict_get with dict_call, "arguments"
    Let pair_count be proc list_count with dict_args
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "Dict call has >= 2 key/value pairs", pair_count, 2

    Note: --- string interpolation inside greet ---
    Let greet_body be proc dict_get with f_greet, "body"
    Let interp be proc find_interpolated_string with greet_body
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "greet has an interpolated string", interp

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils

    Note: A Julia program exercising the full Stage-B construct surface. Each
    Note: function isolates one asserted construct so the depth probes can locate
    Note: it deterministically.
    Let source be "struct Point\nx::Int\ny::Int\nend\nfunction area(r::Int)\nreturn r * r\nend\nfunction scale(x, factor = 2)\nreturn x * factor\nend\nfunction classify(n)\nif n > 0\nreturn 1\nelseif n < 0\nreturn 2\nelse\nreturn 0\nend\nend\nfunction sum_loop(xs)\ntotal = 0\nfor v in xs\ntotal = total + v\nend\nreturn total\nend\nfunction evens(xs)\nreturn [v for v in xs if v > 0]\nend\nfunction config()\nreturn Dict(\"a\" => 1, \"b\" => 2)\nend\nfunction greet(name)\nreturn \"hello $(name) world\"\nend\n"

    Note: --- Stage 0-2: source -> HIR1 ---
    Let hir1 be proc julia_to_hir_from_source from JuliaFrontend with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend produced HIR module", hir1

    Let root_is_module be proc node_is with hir1, "module"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "HIR root is a module", root_is_module, 1

    Let body1 be proc module_body with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "module has a body list", body1

    proc assert_depth with results, hir1, "HIR1"

    Note: --- Stage 3: HIR1 -> Julia text ---
    Let emitted be proc generate_julia_from_hir from JuliaBackend with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "backend produced Julia text", emitted
    Let emitted_len be proc string_length from StringCore with emitted
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "emitted Julia is non-empty", emitted_len, 0

    Note: --- Stage 4: re-parse emitted text -> HIR2 ---
    Let hir2 be proc julia_to_hir_from_source from JuliaFrontend with emitted
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parse of emitted Julia produced HIR2", hir2

    Let root2_is_module be proc node_is with hir2, "module"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip root is a module", root2_is_module, 1

    Note: --- Stage 5: CONTENT survives the round-trip ---
    proc assert_depth with results, hir2, "HIR2"

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process
